mitre_attack_techniques.signature_description: link function at runtime on Windows
Creates an undocumented autostart registry key
Creates files inside the system directory
Drops executable to common a third party application directory
Drops a PE files to the windows directory (C:\\Windows) and starts it
Drops PE files to the windows directory (C:\\Windows)
Mutes Antivirus updates and installments via hosts file black listing
Stores large binary data to the registry
Changes the view of files in windows explorer (hidden files and folders)
Creates files in the recycle bin to hide itself
Sample is looking for USB drives. Launch the sample with the USB Fake Disk cookbook
Infects executable files (exe, dll, sys, html)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects when an attacker tries to disable User Account Control (UAC) by setting the registry value "EnableLUA" to 0.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Disable Internal Tools or Feature in Registry
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects registry modifications that change features of internal Windows tools (malware like Agent Tesla uses this technique)
Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Files With System Process Name In Unsuspected Locations
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects the creation of an executable with a system process name in folders other than the system ones (System32, SysWOW64, etc.).
It is highly recommended to perform an initial baseline before using this rule in production.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Sander Wiebing, Tim Shelton, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)

signature_matches.name: create shortcut via IShellLink
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: create shortcut via IShellLink
    namespace: persistence
    authors:
      - matthew.williams@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: function
      dynamic: unsupported  # requires offset, bytes features
    att&ck:
      - Persistence::Boot or Logon Autostart Execution::Shortcut Modification [T1547.009]
    references:
      - https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/shell/links#creating-a-shortcut-and-a-folder-shortcut-to-a-file
    examples:
      - 7f403f7d643d90c7cbadf3ccfc68bd1badf06f89a35af5fc7811920e820bbcc9:0x10001380
  features:
    - and:
      - bytes: 01 14 02 00 00 00 00 00 C0 00 00 00 00 00 00 46 = CLSID_ShellLink
      - or:
        - bytes: EE 14 02 00 00 00 00 00 C0 00 00 00 00 00 00 46 = IID_IShellLinkA
        - bytes: F9 14 02 00 00 00 00 00 C0 00 00 00 00 00 00 46 = IID_IShellLinkW
      - bytes: 0B 01 00 00 00 00 00 00 C0 00 00 00 00 00 00 46 = IID_IPersistFile
      - offset: 0x50 = psl->SetPath
      - offset: 0x18 = ppf->Save
      - api: ole32.CoCreateInstance

signature_matches.name: enumerate files on Windows

rule:

    name: enumerate files on Windows
    namespace: host-interaction/file-system/files/list
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
      - anushka.virgaonkar@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: function
      dynamic: span of calls
    att&ck:
      - Discovery::File and Directory Discovery [T1083]
    mbc:
      - Discovery::File and Directory Discovery [E1083]
    references:
      - https://github.com/hfiref0x/TDL/blob/cc4b46ae1c939b14a22a734a727b163f873a41b5/Source/Furutaka/sup.c#L315
    examples:
      - Practical Malware Analysis Lab 01-01.exe_:0x4011E0
      - Practical Malware Analysis Lab 20-02.exe_:0x401000
      - 563653399B82CD443F120ECEFF836EA3678D4CF11D9B351BB737573C2D856299:0x14000203C
  features:

          - api: kernel32.FindFirstFileName
          - api: kernel32.FindFirstFileNameTransacted
        - or:
          - api: kernel32.FindNextFile
          - api: kernel32.FindNextFileName
        - optional:
          - api: kernel32.FindClose
          - match: contain loop
      - and:
        - or:
          - basic block:
            - and:
              - number: 1 = DIRECTORY_QUERY
              - api: ntdll.NtOpenDirectoryObject
          - call:
            - and:
              - number: 1 = DIRECTORY_QUERY
              - api: ntdll.NtOpenDirectoryObject
        - api: ntdll.NtQueryDirectoryObject
        - optional:
          - api: RtlAllocateHeap
          - match: contain loop
          - characteristic: indirect call

signature_matches.name: check for time delay via GetTickCount
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: check for time delay via GetTickCount
    namespace: anti-analysis/anti-debugging/debugger-detection
    authors:
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: function
      dynamic: unsupported  # requires mnemonic features
    mbc:
      - Anti-Behavioral Analysis::Debugger Detection::Timing/Delay Check GetTickCount [B0001.032]
    examples:
      - Practical Malware Analysis Lab 16-03.exe_:0x4013d0
  features:
    - and:
      - count(api(kernel32.GetTickCount)): 2 or more
